{"name": "autograd-gamma", "metadata": {"name": "autograd-gamma", "version": "0.5.0", "classifiers": ["Intended Audience :: Science/Research", "Programming Language :: Python :: 2", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Topic :: Scientific/Engineering"], "home_page": "https://github.com/CamDavidsonPilon/autograd-gamma", "license": "MIT License", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Autograd compatible approximations to the gamma family of functions", "upload_time": 1602780666}, "documentation": ["# autograd-gamma\n[![PyPI version](https://badge.fury.io/py/autograd-gamma.svg)](https://badge.fury.io/py/autograd-gamma)\n\n\n[autograd](https://github.com/HIPS/autograd) compatible approximations to the derivatives of the Gamma-family of functions.\n\n\n# Tutorial\n\n```python\nfrom autograd import grad\nfrom autograd_gamma import gammainc, gammaincc, gammaincln, gammainccln\n\n\ngrad(gammainc, argnum=0)(1., 2.)\ngrad(gammaincc, argnum=0)(1., 2.)\n\n# logarithmic functions too.\ngrad(gammaincln, argnum=0)(1., 2.)\ngrad(gammainccln, argnum=0)(1., 2.)\n\n\n\nfrom autograd_gamma import betainc, betaincln\n\ngrad(betainc, argnum=0)(1., 2., 0.5)\ngrad(betainc, argnum=1)(1., 2., 0.5)\n\n# logarithmic functions too.\ngrad(betaincln, argnum=0)(1., 2., 0.5)\ngrad(betaincln, argnum=1)(1., 2., 0.5)\n\n```\n\n\n# Long-term goal\n\nBuild and improve upon the derivative of the upper and lower incomplete gamma functions. Eventually, if we have a fast analytical solution, we will merge into the autograd library."], "modules": [{"name": "setup", "documentation": ["!/usr/bin/env python"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "setup.long_description", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "autograd_gamma", "documentation": ["-*- coding: utf-8 -*-"], "functions": [{"name": "autograd_gamma.gammainccln", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "a", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "x", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "autograd_gamma.gammaincln", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "a", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "x", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "autograd_gamma.betaincln", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "a", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "b", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "x", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "autograd_gamma.central_difference_of_", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "f", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "argnum", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["5th order approximation."]}, {"name": "autograd_gamma.central_difference_of_log", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "f", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "argnum", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["5th order approximation of derivative of log(f). We take advantage of the fact:\n\nd(log(f))/dx = 1/f df/dx\n\nSo we approximate the second term only."]}], "variables": [{"name": "autograd_gamma.LOG_EPISILON", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "autograd_gamma.MACHINE_EPISLON_POWER", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "autograd_gamma.gammainc", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "autograd_gamma.gammaincc", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "autograd_gamma.betainc", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "autograd_gamma.gammainccinv", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "autograd_gamma.gammaincinv", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "autograd_gamma.betaincinv", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "autograd_gamma.beta", "xref": {"fqname": "autograd.scipy.special.beta", "project": null}}, {"name": "autograd_gamma.betainc", "xref": {"fqname": "autograd_gamma.betainc", "project": null}}, {"name": "autograd_gamma.betaincinv",